import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['volume'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Volume')
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['volume'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Trading Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volume?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.plot(data['date'], data['adjclose'], label='Adjusted Close')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted Close')
    plt.title('What is the trend of the S&P 500 index over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'], alpha=0.5)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data['high'], data['low']], labels=['High', 'Low'])
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily high and low prices?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.legend(['High', 'Low'], loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['volume'], data['adjclose'], c=data['date'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted Close')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between trading volume and stock performance?', wrap=True)
    cbar = plt.colorbar(scatter)
    cbar.ax.set_ylabel('Date')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
